obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (7183)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. The words "except the State of Hyderabad" omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1952)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7183&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Central Reserve Police Force Act, 1949.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1`
  line `*** and applies to members of the Force, wherever they may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (7184)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7184&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,—`
  line
  line `(a) "active duty" means the duty to restore and preserve order in any local area in the event of any`
  line `disturbance therein;`
  line
  line `(b) "close arrest" means confinement within the Force or a detachment of the Force or a post`
  line `quarter-guard building or tent under charge of a guard;`
  line
  line `(c) "the Force" means the Central Reserve Police Force;`
  line
  line `(d) "member of the Force" means a person who has been appointed to the Force by the`
  line `Commandant, whether before or after the commencement of this Act, and in sections 1, 3, 6, 7, 16,`
  line `17, 18 and 19, includes also a person appointed to the Force by the Central Government, whether`
  line `before or after such commencement;`
  line
  line `(e) "open arrest" means confinement within the precincts of any barracks, lines or camp for the`
  line `time being occupied by any part of the Force;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "subordinate officer" means a member of the Force of the rank of subedar-major, subedar,`
  line `jemadar or sub-inspector;`
  line
  line `(h) the expressions "assault", "criminal force", "fraudulently", "reason to believe" and`
  line `"voluntarily causing hurt" have the meanings assigned to them respectively in the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860)`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (7185)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7185&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall continue to be an armed force maintained by the`
  line `Central Government and called the Central Reserve Police Force.`
  line
  line `(2) The Force shall be constituted in such manner, and the members of the Force shall receive such`
  line `pay, pension and other remuneration, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (7186)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment and powers of superior officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7186&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may appoint to the`
  line `Force a Commandant and such other persons as it thinks fit to be assistant commandants and company`
  line officers.
  line
  line `(2) The Commandant and every other officer so appointed shall have, and may exercise, such powers`
  line `and authority as may be provided by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (7187)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Enrolment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7187&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Before a person is appointed to be a member of the Force, the statement contained in`
  line `the recruiting roll set out in the Schedule shall be read out and, if necessary, explained to him in the`
  line `presence of an officer appointed under sub-section (1) of section 4, and shall be signed by such person in`
  line `acknowledgement of its having been so read out to him:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person who has for a period of six months served with the Force, shall, on`
  line `appointment to the Force thereafter, be deemed to be a member of the Force notwithstanding that the`
  line `provisions of this section have not been complied with in his case.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (7188)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Resignation and withdrawal from the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7188&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No member of the Force shall be at liberty to—`
  line
  line `(a) resign his appointment during the term of his engagement, except before the expiration of the`
  line `first three months of his service; or`
  line
  line `(b) withdraw himself from all or any of the duties of his appointment, without the previous`
  line `permission in writing of the Commandant or assistant commandant or any other officer authorised by`
  line `the Commandant to grant such permission.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (7189)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `General duties of members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7189&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of every member of the Force`
  line `promptly to obey and to execute all orders and warrants lawfully issued to him by any competent`
  line `authority, to detect and bring offenders to justice and to apprehend all persons whom he is legally`
  line `authorised to apprehend and for whose apprehension sufficient grounds exist.`
  line
  line `(2) Every member of the Force shall be liable to serve without and beyond, as well as within, the`
  line `territory of India`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (7190)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Superintendence, control and administration of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7190&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The superintendence of, and`
  line `control over, the Force shall vest in the Central Government; and the Force shall be administered by the`
  line `Central Government in accordance with the provisions of this Act and of any rules made thereunder,`
  line `through such officers as the Central Government may from time to time appoint in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The Headquarters of the Force shall be at Neemuch or at such other place as may from time to`
  line `time be specified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) While on active duty outside its headquarters, the Force shall be subject to the general control and`
  line `direction of such authority or officer as may be prescribed or as may be specially appointed by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (7191)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `More heinous offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7191&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Force who—`
  line
  line `(a) begins, excites, causes or conspires to cause or joins in any mutiny, or, being present at any`
  line `mutiny, does not use his utmost endeavour to suppress it, or knowing, or having reason to believe in,`
  line `the existence of any mutiny, or of any intention or conspiracy to mutiny or of any conspiracy against`
  line `the State does not, without delay, give information thereof to his superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses, or attempts to use, criminal force to, or commits an assault on, his superior officer,`
  line `whether on or off duty, knowing or having reason to believe him to be such; or`
  line
  line `(c) shamefully abandons or delivers up any post or guard which is committed to his charge, or`
  line `which it is his duty to defend; or`
  line
  line `(d) directly or indirectly holds correspondence with, or assists or relieves any person in arms`
  line `against the State or omits to discover immediately to his superior officer any such correspondence`
  line `coming to his knowledge ; or`
  line
  line `who, while on active duty,—`
  line
  line `(e) disobeys the lawful command of his superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(f) deserts the Force; or`
  line
  line `(g) being a sentry, sleeps upon his post or quits it without being regularly relieved or without`
  line `leave; or`
  line
  line `(h) leaves his commanding officer, or his post or party, to go in search of plunder; or`
  line
  line `(i) quits his guard, picquet, party or patrol without being regularly relieved or without leave; or`
  line
  line `(j) uses criminal force to, or commits an assault on, any person bringing provisions or other`
  line `necessaries to camp or quarters, or forces a safeguard or breaks into any house or other place for`
  line `plunder, or plunders, destroys or damages property of any kind; or`
  line
  line `(k) intentionally causes or spreads a false alarm in action or in camp, garrison or quarters; or`
  line
  line `(l) displays cowardice in the execution of his duty,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with transportation for life for a term of not less than seven years or with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen years or with fine which may extend to three`
  line `months pay or with fine to that extent in addition to such sentence of transportation or imprisonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (7192)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Less heinous offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7192&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Force who—`
  line
  line `(a) is in a state of intoxication when on, or after having been warned for, any duty or on parade or`
  line `on the line of march; or`
  line
  line `(b) strikesor attempts to force any sentry; or`
  line
  line `(c) being in command of a guard, picquet or patrol, refuses to receive any prisoner or person duly`
  line `committed to his charge, or without proper authority releases any person or prisoner placed under his`
  line `charge, or negligently suffers any such prisoner or person to escape; or`
  line
  line `(d) being under arrest or in confinement, leaves his arrest or confinement, before he is set at`
  line `liberty by lawful authority; or`
  line
  line `(e) is grossly insubordinate or insolvent to his superior officer in the execution of his office; or`
  line
  line `(f) refuses to superintend or assist in the making of any field-work or other work of any`
  line `description ordered to be made either in quarters or in the field; or`
  line
  line `(g) strikes or otherwise ill-uses any member of the Force subordinate to him in rank or position;`
  line or
  line
  line `(h) designedly or through neglect injuries or loses or fraudulently disposes of his arms, clothes,`
  line `tools, equipments, ammunition or accoutrements, or any such articles entrusted to him or belonging to`
  line `any other person; or`
  line
  line `(i) malingers or feigns or produces disease or infirmity in himself, or intentionally delays his cure,`
  line `or aggravates his disease or infirmity; or`
  line
  line `(j) with intent to render himself or any other person unfit for service, voluntarily causes hurt to`
  line `himself or any other person; or`
  line
  line `(k) does not, when called upon by his superior officer so to do or upon ceasing to be a member of`
  line `the Force forthwith deliver up, or duly account for, all or any arms, ammunition, stores,`
  line `accoutrements or other property issued or supplied to him or in his custody or possession as such`
  line `member; or`
  line
  line `(l) knowingly furnishes a false return or report of the number or state of any men under his`
  line `command or charge or of any money, arms, ammunition, clothing, equipments, stores or other`
  line `property in his charge, whether belonging to such men or to the Government or to any member of, or`
  line `any person attached to the Force, or who, through design or culpable neglect, omits or refuses to`
  line `make or send any return or report of the matters aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(m) absents himself without leave, or without sufficient cause over-stays leave granted to him; or`
  line
  line `(n) is guilty of any act or omission which, though not specified in this Act, is prejudicial to good`
  line `order and discipline; or`
  line
  line `(o) contravenes any provision of this Act for which no punishment is expressly provided; or`
  line
  line `who, while not on active duty—,`
  line
  line `(p) commits any of the offences specified in clauses (e) to (l) (both inclusive) of section 9,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to three months' pay, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (7193)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Minor punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7193&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commandant or any other authority or officer as may be`
  line `prescribed, may, subject to any rules made under this Act, award in lieu of, or in addition to, suspension`
  line `or dismissal any one or more of the following punishments to any member of the Force whom he`
  line `considers to be guilty of disobedience, neglect of duty, or remissness in the discharge of any duty or of`
  line `other misconduct in his capacity as a member of the Force, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) reduction in rank;`
  line
  line `(b)fine of any amount not exceeding one month's pay and allowances;`
  line
  line `(c) confinement to quarters, lines or camp for a term not exceeding one month;`
  line
  line `(d) confinement in the quarter-guard for not more than twenty-eight days, with or without`
  line `punishment drill or extra guard, fatigue or other duty; and`
  line
  line `(e) removal from any office of distinction or special emolument in the Force.`
  line
  line `(2) Any punishment specified in clause (c) or clause (d) of sub-section (1) may be awarded by any`
  line `gazetted officer when in command of any detachment of the Force away from headquarters, provided he`
  line `is specially authorised in this behalf by the Commandant.`
  line
  line `(3) The assistant commandant, a company officer or a subordinate officer, not being below the rank`
  line `of subedar or inspector, commanding a separate detachment or an outpost, or in temporary command at`
  line `the headquarters of the Force, may, without a formal trial, award to any member of the Force who is for`
  line `the time being subject to his authority any one or more of the following punishments for the commission`
  line `of any petty offence against discipline which is not otherwise provided for in this Act, or which is not of a`
  line `sufficiently serious nature to require prosecution before a criminal Court, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) confinement for not more than seven days in the quarter-guard or such other place as may be`
  line `considered suitable, with forfeiture of all pay and allowances during its continuance;`
  line
  line `(b) punishment drill, or extra guard, fatigue or other duty, for not more than thirty days, with or`
  line `without confinement to quarters, lines or camp;`
  line
  line `(c) censure or severe censure:provided that this punishment may be awarded to a subordinate`
  line `officer only by the Commandant.`
  line
  line `(4) A jemadar or sub-inspector who is temporarily in command of a detachment or an outpost may, in`
  line `like manner and for the commission of any like offence, award to any member of the Force for the time`
  line `being subject to his authority any of the punishments specified in clause (b) of sub-section (3) for not`
  line `more than fifteen days.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (7194)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Place of imprisonment and liability to dismissal on imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7194&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person`
  line `sentenced under this Act to imprisonment may be dismissed from the Force, and shall further be liable to`
  line `forfeiture of pay, allowance and any other moneys due to him, as well as of any medals and decorations`
  line `received by him.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such person shall, if he is so dismissed, be imprisoned in the prescribed prison, but if he is`
  line `not also dismissed from the Force, he may, if the Court or the Commandant so directs, be confined in the`
  line `quarter-guard or such other place as the Court or the Commandant may consider suitable.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (7195)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Deductions from pay and allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7195&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The following penal deductions may be made from the`
  line `pay and allowances of a member of the Force by his company officer, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) all pay and allowances for every day of absence either on desertion or without leave and for`
  line `every day of imprisonment awarded by a criminal Court or of confinement awarded under section 11;`
  line
  line `(b) all pay and allowances for every day whilst he is in custody on a charge for an offence of`
  line `which he is afterwards convicted;`
  line
  line `(c) all pay and allowances for every day on which he is in hospital on account of sickness`
  line `certified by the medical officer attending on him at the hospital to have been caused by an offence`
  line `committed by him under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) all pay and allowances ordered to be forfeited under section 11; and`
  line
  line `(e) such sum as may be ordered by the Commandant or assistant commandant in order to make`
  line `good any expenses caused by the member of the Force, or any loss of, or damage or destruction done`
  line `by him to, any arms, ammunition, equipment, clothing, instruments or decorations belonging to the`
  line `Force or to any buildings or property.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (7196)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Collective fines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7196&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any weapon, part of a weapon or ammunition, forming part of the`
  line `equipment of a company or other similar unit of the Force, is lost or stolen the Commandant may, after`
  line `making such inquiry as he thinks fit and subject to such rules as may be prescribed, impose a collective`
  line `fine upon the subordinate officers and men of such unit, or upon so many of them as, in his judgment,`
  line `should be held responsible for such loss or theft.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (7197)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title Arrest.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7197&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any member of the Force who commits any offence specified in section 9 or section`
  line `10 may be placed on open or close arrest by any officer of the Force.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any subordinate officer orders an arrest under sub-section (1), he shall forthwith or at the`
  line `earliest opportunity report the arrest to his company or detachment commander who shall after`
  line `investigating the case order the release or the continued arrest of the member of the Force arrested.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (7198)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Powers and duties conferrable and imposable on members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7198&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by general or special order, confer or impose upon any member of the force any of the`
  line `powers or duties conferred or imposed on a police officer of any class or grade by any law for the time`
  line `being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), the`
  line `Central Government may invest the Commandant or an assistant commandant with the powers of a`
  line `Magistrate of any class for the purpose of inquiring into or trying any offence committed by a member of`
  line `the Force and punishable under this Act, or any offence committed by a member of the Force against the`
  line `person or property of another member:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(i) when the offender is on leave or absent from duty, or`
  line
  line `(ii) when the offence is not connected with the offender's duties as a member of the Force, or`
  line
  line `(iii) when it is a petty offence, even if connected with the offender's duties as a member of the`
  line Force,
  line
  line `the offence may, if the prescribed authority within the limits of whose jurisdiction the offence has been`
  line `committed, so directs, be inquired into or tried by an ordinary criminal Court having jurisdiction in the`
  line matter.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (7199)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Protection for acts of members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7199&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any suit or proceeding against any`
  line `member of the Force for any act done by him in pursuance of a warrant or order of a competent authority, it shall be lawful for him to plead that such act was done by him under the authority of such warrant or`
  line order.
  line
  line `(2) Any such plea may be proved by the production of the warrant or order directing the act, and if it`
  line `is so proved the member of the Force shall thereupon be discharged from liability in respect of the act so`
  line `done by him, notwithstanding any defect in the jurisdiction of the authority which issued such warrant or`
  line order.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, any legal`
  line `proceeding (whether civil or criminal) which may lawfully be brought against any member of the Force`
  line `for anything done or intended to be done under the powers conferred by, or in pursuance of, any provision`
  line `of this Act or the rules thereunder, shall be commenced within three months after the act complained of`
  line `was committed and not otherwise, and notice in, writing of such proceeding and of the cause thereof shall`
  line `be given to the defendant or his superior officer at least one month before the commencement of such`
  line proceeding.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (7200)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `2. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7200&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the classes and grades of, and the pay, pension and other remuneration of, members`
  line `of the Force, and their conditions of service in the Force;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the powers and duties of officers authorised to exercise any functions by or under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) fixing the period of service for members of the Force;`
  line
  line `(d) regulating the award of minor punishments under section 11, and providing for appeals from,`
  line `or the revision of, orders under that section, or the remission of fines imposed under that section, and`
  line `the remission of deductions made under section 13;`
  line
  line `(e) regulating the several or collective liability of members of the Force in the case of the loss or`
  line `theft of weapons and ammunition;`
  line
  line `(f) for the disposal of criminal cases arising under this Act and for specifying the prison in which`
  line `a person convicted in any such case may be confined.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (7201)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Validation of acts done before commencement of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820&sectionId=7201&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00006_194966_1517807319820
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Any order made, thing done, or action`
  line `taken by or in relation to a member of the Force, on or after the 15th day of August, 1947, but before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, shall for all purposes be deemed to have been made, done or taken under this`
  line `Act as if this Act were in force on the day on which such order was made, thing was done or action was`
  line taken.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
